<p>Figures 5 and 6 show the take-up rate of employments furloughed within each country and region using <abbr title="Coronavirus Job Retention Scheme">CJRS</abbr>, with figure 6 providing a gender breakdown.</p>

<p>The key points to note from figures 5 and 6 are as at 31 July (provisional figures):</p>

<ul>
  <li>in figure 5, preliminary estimates show there was broad consistency in furlough rates across the nations and regions of the UK at the end of July (provisional data). London had the highest take-up rate of 17% against the UK average of 16%</li>
  <li>as shown in figure 6, preliminary estimates show that the take up rate is similar for men and women across all regions and countries of the UK</li>
</ul>

